  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>systemd-remove-attempts.service</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>8</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>systemd-remove-attempts.service</refname>
    <refname>systemd-remove-attempts</refname>
    <refpurpose>Removes attempts configuration file from the EFI System Partition</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <para><filename>systemd-remove-attempts.service</filename></para>
    <para><filename>/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-remove-attempts</filename></para>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para><filename>systemd-remove-attempts.service</filename> is an oneshot
    late boot service that removes attempts configuration file. Path to file
    which should be removed is handed over by OS loader in the EFI variable
    <envar>LoaderAttemptsPath</envar>. Service will remove the file, indicating
    to OS loader that coresponding boot loader entry should be considered valid
    on next reboot.</para>
  </refsect1>

